cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper deals with network coding problems and their capacity regions, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers linear encoding constraints, routing constraints, and secrecy constraints, which are relevant to the sub-categories of security and privacy (cs.SI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
